Did you know you can do this!?<p><pre><code>  someObject.foo = function() {
    someObject.bar = 123;
  }

  function Foo() {
    var Foo = this;
    Foo.bar = 456;
  }
</code></pre>
Pro tip: Always do asynchronous operations Before presenting the object to the program state. Or you will see &quot;undefined&quot; bugs in production!
